FruitsVegProduct.name: Watermelon (Tarbuj) 1kg
FruitsVegProduct.description: Kiran watermelon is a small to medium-sized variety of watermelon. It has a dark green rind with emerald-black undertones and its flesh is dark red,crisp,and slightly grainy. They have a refreshing,light,and sweet taste and can be eaten raw,sliced,or chilled in the fridge.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Chikoo (Sapota) 400-500gm
FruitsVegProduct.description: Sapota, also known as chikoo or sapodilla, is a tropical fruit with a unique sweet and caramel-like flavor. Sapota is often enjoyed fresh as a dessert fruit or used in milkshakes, ice creams, and smoothies.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Papaya (Papita) 500gm -1kg
FruitsVegProduct.description: Papaya is delicious eaten fresh, blended into smoothies, or used in salads and desserts.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Apple (Seb)500gm
FruitsVegProduct.description: Small Shimla apples are crisp, sweet, and perfect for snacking. Enjoy their juicy flavor as a healthy treat or add them to salads for a refreshing crunch.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Safeda / Banganapalli Mango 2 pieces (550-700 g)
FruitsVegProduct.description: Safeda mangoes, also known as Banganapalli mangoes, are large, juicy mangoes with a sweet and slightly tangy flavor. They have a smooth, yellow skin and firm flesh, making them ideal for slicing and enjoying fresh or using in smoothies and desserts.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Muskmelon (Kharbuja) 1 piece (400-600 g)
FruitsVegProduct.description: Sweet and succulent musk melon, bursting with refreshing flavor. A perfect choice for a healthy and hydrating snack. Muskmelons are commonly enjoyed fresh as a snack or used in fruit salads, smoothies, and desserts.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Pomegranate (Anar) 2 pieces (400 g -500 g)
FruitsVegProduct.description: Pomegranate has a juicy cluster of sparkling, opaque, red coloured seeds which taste sweet. It can be used for topping desserts and to make juices and fruit salads.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Raw Mango (kachhe aam) (200-300) g
FruitsVegProduct.description: Unripe mango is a stone fruit known for its tangy, sour taste. Smaller in size with a thin, smooth, green coloured skin, raw mangoes are widely used in pickles and chutneys.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Sweet Lime (Mosambi) 1 kg (9-10 pieces)
FruitsVegProduct.description: Mosambi, also known as sweet lime, is a citrus fruit with a mild, sweet flavor and refreshing juiciness. Enjoy it fresh for a naturally sweet and thirst-quenching experience.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Pineapple (Ananas) 1 piece (800-1000 g)
FruitsVegProduct.description: Healthy and nutritious, Pineapple is a sweet and juicy fruit that makes for a delicious addition to salads. It is perfect for garnishing cocktails and other drinks and can be used for stir-fry cooking.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Langra Mango 2 pieces (400 - 600) g
FruitsVegProduct.description: Currently Langra mango is sourced from Gujrat. Early season variety is known for their sweetness as well as aromatic qualities and juicy flesh. Best enjoyed for eating as is, and they can be used in salads, desserts, shakes, ice cream and other mango-based dishes also.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Totapuri Mango 2 pieces (600-800 g)
FruitsVegProduct.description: Totapuri mangoes are prized for their tangy-sweet flavor and firm texture. Ideal for eating fresh, making juices, or adding a tropical twist to salads and chutneys. They have a parrot-like beak at the fruit tip and greenish yellow skin.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Grapes (Hara Angoor) 500 g
FruitsVegProduct.description: Green grapes are nutritional berries with a sweet-sour taste. Grapes are a great, naturally sweet treat if you are trying to reduce your sugar intake. Grapes are most often eaten fresh, out-of-hand, or sliced and mixed into green salads, yogurt, or veggie wraps.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Coriander leaves with roots (Dhaniya Patta), 100gm
FruitsVegProduct.description: Coriander leaves, also known as cilantro, Aromatic green leaves that are largely used to flavour and garnish food. When added to heated dishes, the leaves lose their flavour, and are often used raw or garnished just before serving.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Desi Tomato (Tamatar) 500gm + Free Dhaniya
FruitsVegProduct.description: Tomatoes are a significant source of umami flavor.The tomato is consumed in diverse ways, raw or cooked, in many dishes, sauces, salads, and drinks. While tomatoes are fruits—botanically classified as berries—they are commonly used culinarily as a vegetable ingredient or side dish.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Lady Finger (Bhindi) 250gm + Free Dhaniya
FruitsVegProduct.description: A highly versatile vegetable in the Indian cuisine, Lady Finger can be sliced or chopped or can be paired with other vegetables for an exquisite taste. Toss in some green chillies or onions for a flavourful, wholesome main course dish.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Fresh Potato (Aaloo) - 1kg + Free Dhaniya
FruitsVegProduct.description: Potato is a starchy vegetable that is widely used in many recipes. Due to its bland taste, peeled potatoes can be mixed with a number of vegetables. Potatoes are also used in making chips and snacks.

FruitsVegProduct.name: Green Chilli 100gm (Hari Mirch) + Free Dhaniya

FruitsVegProduct.name: Brinjal Bharta (Baingan) 2pc (400-600)g + Free Daniya

FruitsVegProduct.name: Cabbage (Patta Gobhi) 1 piece (400-600 g)

FruitsVegProduct.name: Ginger (Adrak) 200g
